{"id":"190","name":"bright-early-fire-up-the-grill-edition","title":"Bright &amp; Early: Fire Up The Grill Edition","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2008-05-26T09:00:00-05:00","tags":[],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/2522515547_fb8a0e291f.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-191\" title=\"2522515547_fb8a0e291f\" src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/2522515547_fb8a0e291f.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"325\"></a></p><p>Good morning, Nashville. Hopefully your grills are good and ready to ring in the unofficial start of summer. But watch out for the lightning, since Nashville WX is <a href=\"http://nashvillewx.com/2008/05/25/scattered-storms-for-memorial-day-respect-lightning/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillewx.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">warning us</a> about some nasty storms that may be edging their way into our Memorial Day plans. If you&#x2019;re in need of some last-minute pointers, check out <a href=\"http://lifehacker.com/392818/become-the-memorial-day-grill-master\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;lifehacker.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Lifehacker</a> (one of Nashvillest&#x2019;s favorite reads) for tips on mastering the art of the Tennessee grill-out. And if you&#x2019;re too lazy to cook, be sure to check out <a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2008/05/23/memorial-day-2008-too-lazy-to-grill-out/\" target=\"_blank\">Nashvillest&#x2019;s guide</a> to Memorial Day 2008.</p><ul><li><strong>Working for a living.</strong> Good news on the job front.<strong> </strong>Nearly 40 big companies are thinking about building or relocating corporate offices to Nashville, which could bring <a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=8374625\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">thousands of jobs</a> to the Middle Tennessee region. Just probably not in time to accommodate the 2,000 state employees who are about to be laid off.</li><li><strong>Thrills and spills. </strong>Over the weekend, Lipscomb&#x2019;s baseball team <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20080525/SPORTS060403/80525004/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">won the Atlantic Sun tournament</a> in 15 innings to earn themselves a spot in the NCAA tournament. Vandy, on the other hand, <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20080524/SPORTS0602/80524018/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">was eliminated</a> from the Southeastern Conference after a well-fought 8-7 loss to Ole Miss.</li><li><strong>Bits &amp; pieces. </strong>Immigration status won&#x2019;t be <a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/news/16390129/detail.html?rss=nash&amp;psp=news\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">affecting marriage rights</a> anymore in Davidson Co. &#x2026; Bald eagle <a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=8374284\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_self\">sighting</a> at Radnor Lake &#x2026; Rutherford Co. apparently has a &#x201C;wheel tax&#x201D; where they tax the wheels on your car, and now they want to <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=8372823\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">raise it</a> &#x2026; The guys in Colombia, TN who burned down that mosque a few months ago are set to <a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/news/16384922/detail.html?rss=nash&amp;psp=news\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">go to trial</a> in September &#x2026; We may see <a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/automotive/16373806/detail.html?rss=nash&amp;psp=news\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">$5 gas by Labor Day</a>, which is when Nashvillest stops driving.</li></ul><p><em>Photo by <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/crashmattb/2522515547/in/pool-nashvillest\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">crashmattb</a>.</em></p><p>No related posts.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}